Definition.WordDefinition: Homogenous \Ho*mog"e*nous\, a. (Biol.) Having a resemblance in structure, due to descent from a common progenitor with subsequent modification; homogenetic; -- applied both to animals and plants. See {Homoplastic}. [1913 Webster]
homogenous adj : all of the same or similar kind or nature; "a close-knit homogeneous group" [syn: {homogeneous}] [ant: {heterogeneous}]
